Czech PX Stock Index Drops From Month High as CEZ Shares Retreat

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-07-04T14:42:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/czech-px-stock-index-drops-from-month-high-as-cez-shares-retreat.html
The Czech Republic’s main stock index
fell from the highest in a month after declines at  CEZ AS (CEZ) , the
country’s biggest power producer, and  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB) 
outweighed gains at  Erste Group Bank AG. (RBAG)   The PX gauge slid 0.3 percent to 1,231.6 at its 4:28 p.m.
close in Prague. CEZ, which has an 18 percent weighting in the
index, dropped 1.7 percent to 852 koruna. Komercni, the Czech
unit of Societe Generale SA, fell 0.6 percent to 4,075 koruna.
Erste shares climbed 0.4 percent to 886 koruna.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
